<TITLE> Police say 1 dead, 1 'critical' in UP shooting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)One person was killed as Sultanganj Union Parishad chairman Monir Hossain shot into a crowd of angry protestors in Kamrangirchar on Tuesday, said local police. "Another, whom we feared dead after a gunshot to the head, has survived, but is in critical condition," said deputy police commissioner of Lalbagh Zone Abdul Malek. Local police had earlier reported two people dead as Hossain fired at an angry mob that had surrounded his car in an altercation. Malek said the dead man's identity was confirmed as 18 year-old woodworker 'Hasan'. Mahfuzur Rahman,a fellow woodshop worker, said Hasan received a bullet in the chest as the chairman opened fire at an angry mob in the middle of a heated dispute. Hasan was rushed to Mitford Hospital around 3pm where the duty doctor declared him dead, said Mahfuz. Eye-witness 'Rony' told bdnews24.com that the protestors had laid siege to the UP chairman in his car over the expansion of a local road. The crowd had laid siege to his car as Hossain was trying to leave the scene of the protests, said Rony. After the shooting, Hossain managed to flee in his car, but hundreds of furious locals went on to attack his Ashrafabad residence. The mob set fire to his garage, burning a second vehicle belonging to the chairmanan SUV. Lalbagh Zone fire brigade's senior officer Manikujjaman said firefighters rushed to the spot to extinguish the blaze, bringing it under control at around 3.30pm bdnews2
